This paper discusses the design aspects and challenges of caching at the wireless edge, which is a topic related to networking and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses methods to predict popularity distributions and user preferences, which involves data analysis and machine learning techniques, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses content placement and delivery, which involves optimization and algorithm design, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category. The paper also discusses limitations and trade-offs in wireless caching, which involves system design and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper mentions the impact of caching on spectral efficiency and energy consumption, which involves multimedia processing and optimization, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a less likely but still possible category.
